<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 7:08AM CDT  by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Glasscock,
southwestern Mitchell, northeastern Reagan and southeastern Howard
Counties through 800 AM CDT...
At 708 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Garden City, moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Garden City, Forsan and Saint Lawrence.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
